:["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":4,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Ingleby was born about 1378, in Ripley, Yorkshire, England, his father, John Ingleby, was 24 and his mother, Ellen Rocliffe, was 29. He had at least 1 son with Ellen Holm. He died in 1420, in his hometown, at the age of 43, and was buried in Ripley, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"about 1378–1420":"umbes 1378–1420","1378–1420":"1378–1420","1395–1430":"1395–1430","1413–1438":"1413–1438","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1350–1400":"1350–1400","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","about 1378":"umbes 1378","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1438":"1438","Ripley, Yorkshire, England":"Ripley, Yorkshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1378–1420":"noin 1378–1420","1378–1420":"1378–1420","1395–1430":"1395–1430","1413–1438":"1413–1438","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1350–1400":"1350–1400","1413":"1413","1400":"1400","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","1430":"1430","about 1378":"noin 1378","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1438":"1438","Ripley, Yorkshire, England":"Ripley, Yorkshire, England","England":"Eng